<troubleshooting id="syntax-highlight-not-available-Eclipse-plugin">
  <title>Syntax Highlights Not Available in Eclipse Plugin</title>
  <troublebody><condition id="problem">
      <title>Problem</title>
      <p id="p_oyk_dgk_54b">I associated the <codeph>.ext</codeph> extension with <ph keyref="product"/> in Eclipse but
        an <codeph>.ext</codeph> file opened with the <ph keyref="product"/> plugin does not have
        syntax highlights.</p>
    </condition><troubleSolution><remedy id="solution">
      <title>Solution</title>
        <steps-informal>
          <p id="p_pyk_dgk_54b">Associate an extension with <ph keyref="product"/> in Eclipse versions <ph
              keyref="currentSupportedEclipseVersions"/> by following these steps:<ol id="ol_qyk_dgk_54b">
              <li id="li_ryk_dgk_54b">Associate the <codeph>.ext</codeph> extension with the <ph keyref="product"/> plugin:<ol id="ol_syk_dgk_54b">
                  <li id="li_tyk_dgk_54b"><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/> and go
                    to <menucascade>
                      <uicontrol>General</uicontrol>
                      <uicontrol>Editors</uicontrol>
                      <uicontrol>File Associations</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</li>
                  <li id="li_uyk_dgk_54b">Add <codeph>*.ext</codeph> to the list of file types.</li>
                  <li id="li_vyk_dgk_54b">Select <codeph>*.ext</codeph> in the list by clicking it.</li>
                  <li id="li_wyk_dgk_54b">Add <ph keyref="product"/> to the list of <uicontrol>Associated
                      editors</uicontrol> and make it the default editor.</li>
                </ol></li>
              <li id="li_xyk_dgk_54b">Associate the <codeph>.ext</codeph> extension with the <uicontrol>Oxygen
                  XML</uicontrol> content type:<ol id="ol_yyk_dgk_54b">
                  <li id="li_zyk_dgk_54b"><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/> and go
                    to <menucascade>
                      <uicontrol>General</uicontrol>
                      <uicontrol>Content Types</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</li>
                  <li id="li_azk_dgk_54b">Add <codeph>*.ext</codeph> to the <uicontrol>File associations</uicontrol>
                    list for the <menucascade>
                      <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol>
                      <uicontrol>XML</uicontrol>
                      <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
                    </menucascade> content type.</li>
                </ol></li>
              <li id="li_bzk_dgk_54b">Click the <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol> button in the Eclipse preferences dialog
                box.</li>
            </ol></p>
          <p id="p_czk_dgk_54b"><b>Result:</b> Now when an <codeph>*.ext</codeph> file is opened, the icon and the
            syntax highlights should be the same as for XML files opened with the <ph
              keyref="product"/> plugin.</p>
        </steps-informal>
    </remedy></troubleSolution></troublebody>
</troubleshooting>
